    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Refers to the the culture, style, and period associated with the Qin dynasty, the first imperial Chinese dynasty, dating from 221-206 BCE. It was during this time that the Great Wall was constructed. Few art objects can be definitely attributed to this period, the best known being life-size pottery soldiers and horses found at the tomb of King Zheng in Lintong.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
